A man died in Elysian Park when a hillside collapsed on his tent, while another man and his children were rescued from a collapsed hillside home in Studio City.
Stormy weather in Southern California caused power outages, stranded cars, and multiple rescues.
Mudslides and flooding led to road closures, accidents, and evacuations across the region.
Union Pacific faced transportation challenges due to washed-out tracks, impacting freight traffic.
The relentless rain and snow have caused chaos, with concerns about more mudslides and ongoing rescue efforts.
Despite the challenges, the moisture brings hope for the arid West.
